Environment: Next.js 15 App Router app at hols.meavo.app (Meavo satellite app). Users/teams/access live in the shared gateway database — this app owns only vacation data.

## Stack

- Next.js 15 App Router, TypeScript strict, React 19
- Prisma 6 via `@meavo/db` → shared Neon Postgres (same DB as meavo-gateway)
- NextAuth v5 JWT (Credentials + invite-only Google)
- Tailwind CSS 3, in-house kit `src/components/ui.tsx`, `@meavo/navigation` nav
- FullCalendar, date-fns; Vercel hosting + cron; optional Slack webhook

## Do NOT

- Edit the Prisma schema here — schema lives in meavo-db; `npm run db:push` is disabled on purpose
- Create/edit users, teams, or tool access — gateway owns those; hols reads them
- Skip `getHolsUser()` / `requireHolsUser()` in Server Actions or API routes
- Import `@/lib/auth` in `src/middleware.ts` (edge) — use `@/lib/auth.config` only
- Add shadcn/Radix/MUI or a custom top nav
- Send email from this app — enqueue to `NotificationOutbox` instead
- Let Slack/outbox side effects block or fail a mutation
- Commit secrets or `.env*` files

## Code layout

| Area | Path |
|------|------|
| Authenticated pages | `src/app/(app)/` (calendar `page.tsx`, `requests/`, `approvals/`, `admin/`, `profile/`) |
| Server Actions | `src/app/actions/` (`vacation.ts`, `admin.ts`, `auth.ts`) |
| API routes | `src/app/api/` (calendar feed, cron, health, NextAuth) |
| Domain logic | `src/lib/` (`allowance.ts`, `dates.ts`, `permissions.ts`, `public-holidays.ts`) |
| Auth & access | `src/lib/access.ts`, `src/lib/auth.ts`, `src/lib/auth.config.ts`, `src/middleware.ts` |
| Integrations | `src/lib/slack.ts`, `src/lib/notifications/enqueue.ts` |
| UI components | `src/components/` (kit in `ui.tsx`) |
| Tests | N/A — no test suite |

## Data flow

```
Browser → Server Action (src/app/actions/*)
        → getHolsUser() access check
        → validation + write in one Serializable prisma.$transaction
        → fire-and-forget: Slack webhook + NotificationOutbox enqueue
        → revalidatePath() for affected routes
Calendar UI → GET /api/calendar → approved requests + cached public holidays
Vercel cron (daily) → /api/cron/sync-holidays → Nager.Date API → PublicHoliday table
```

Every request write that others should hear about must enqueue `hols.vacation.{requested|approved|rejected}` via `enqueueNotification()`; only gateway sends email.

